Date:  26/8/1882
Source:  Taranaki Herald
Author:
Vol / Page:  2
Edition:
Quote:  We rode up, and received the first confirmation of our fears; they told us that no one would venture in with despatches, that the troops were driven clean off the field and left their dead and wounded. The expression used was "They ran like red shanks."
Notes:

Date:  19/11/1910
Source:  NZ Truth
Author:
Vol / Page:  282/1/2
Edition:
Quote:  Dr. Findlay, who is nick-named the Government apologist, ran like a red shank until he got the ear of a reporter, and to him he confided his utter astonishment at such a change being made by a retired magistrate against his administration.
